text: Alegazovo () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Alegazovsky Selsoviet, Mechetlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 1,341 as of 2010. There are 18 streets. == Geography == It is located 12 km from Bolsheustyikinskoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mechetlinsky District
title: Alegazovo
